<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD AND BLACK AMERICANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am amused, and somewhat bemused too, at one Benjamin Stein's plea for more 
roles for blacks in the movies. As a black man myself, I think Stein asks too 
much. 
</P>
<P>
For example: I'm not a big TV fan, but it does seem to me that there are more 
black shows on the air than there are white. In every movie, blacks have 
leading roles, very often where they would not be found in everyday life. 
</P>
<P>
About 10 years ago, several black movies were made, and apparently they lost 
money. As a black, I am not interested in paying to see other people who are my 
color: I need more motivation than that. I think we blacks now have more than 
our fair share on film and that it's time to give that plea a rest. 
</P>
<P>
GABRIEL FURLONG 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
