<HEADLINE>
<P>
MECHANIC FATALLY SHOT AT PACOIMA AUTO SHOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A caretaker at a Pacoima auto repair business fatally shot a Sun Valley man who 
had been working on a car there Tuesday, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Carlos Daneal Costa, 22, was pronounced dead at the scene in the 13200 block of 
Van Nuys Boulevard, Detective Al Ferrand said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect, a Latino described as 28 to 30 years old, fled, perhaps in a beige 
1965 Chevrolet Impala, Ferrand said. 
</P>
<P>
Police had not determined a motive in the slaying. Ferrand said it did not 
appear that robbery was a motive, nor was there any evidence that the victim 
was involved in gangs or drugs. 
</P>
<P>
Ferrand described Costa as a free-lance auto mechanic who paid a fee to use the 
facility for car repairs. Witnesses told police they heard a shot and saw the 
gunman looking down at the victim. Police said the two may have known each 
other, but the nature of the relationship was unknown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
