<P>
LEARNING TO READ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is very annoying to know that illiteracy has become an accumulated problem 
in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
Possibly, literacy centers could be made to help assist people in learning. Or, 
with all of the different teaching aids for literate people, maybe these same 
companies could make teaching aids for the illiterate. The libraries could 
offer free classes to develop reading and writing skills. Correctional 
facilities should automatically make prisoners attend classes. 
</P>
<P>
RANDY RETTIG 
</P>
