<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON GOVERNMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I feel battered by my government. Five senators have time to plead for a 
savings and loan tycoon, and trauma centers close; we invade Panama, killing 
our own and Panamanians, spending millions and the President tells a Texas drug 
rehabilitation center that there are no federal funds to assist; we debate 
whether we should execute drug dealers, and close libraries and deny funds to 
our schools. 
</P>
<P>
Is this the government American people want? 
</P>
<P>
JANE EGLY 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 
</P>
