<P>
Paramount Communications Inc.: The New York-based entertainment conglomerate 
reported fiscal 1989 profit of $1.47 billion, up sharply from $385 million a 
year ago, largely due to a $1.2-billion gain on the sale of its Associates 
First Capital Corp. finance unit to a Ford Motor Co. subsidiary. Revenue 
excluding the Associates sale totaled $3.4 billion, up 10%. The firm, which 
changed its name from Gulf &amp; Western Industries Inc., also took a 
$48-million charge for costs incurred in its failed bid for Time Inc. 
</P>
