<P>
'Today' Picking New Boss: With Deborah Norville debuting in Jane Pauley's place 
on NBC's "Today" show this week, the network was also selecting a new boss for 
the series. Top candidates reportedly included Tom Capra, the news director who 
led KNBC Channel 4 to the top of the ratings; Steve Friedman, former head of 
"Today"; and the series' current executive producer, Marty Ryan. The job opened 
up when negotiations between "Entertainment Tonight" producer David Nuell and 
"Today" fell through. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
