<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Most Nods for Soul II Soul The British group Soul II Soul outdistanced dance 
music divas Paula Abdul and Janet Jackson to grab the most Dance Music Award 
nominations announced Monday. The award honors the year's most popular and 
innovative dance tunes and the musicians and record companies behind them. 
</P>
<P>
Nominations and winners are selected by disc jockeys and nightclub operators 
nationwide in addition to a 50-member advisory board of record label 
executives. A newcomer to the American Music scene, Soul II Soul was nominated 
in six of 21 categories including best dance group, best dance artist and best 
new artist on a major label. Abdul, Jackson and Bobby Brown were runners-up 
with four nominations apiece. The second annual awards event will be held at 
the Universal Ampitheater on Feb. 12. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
