<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BOY, 14, SHOT TO DEATH IN DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
AT PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 14-year-old boy was shot to death and a 19-year-old man was wounded Tuesday 
afternoon in a drive-by shooting at a Santa Fe Springs park. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting, which sheriff's investigators said may be gang-related, occurred 
about 3:30 p.m. at Little Lake Park after an argument between a group of 
teen-agers and a carload of men cruising past. Following the verbal 
altercation, witnesses and investigators said, the people in the car pulled a 
gun from beneath the hood of their vehicle and opened fire. 
</P>
<P>
The 14-year-old was shot in the chest, and the other victim was wounded in the 
leg. Names of the victims were withheld pending notification of relatives. 
</P>
