<P>
LAUREL RACES CANCELED TUESDAY BECAUSE OF TRACK CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAUREL, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Racing was canceled after the fourth race Tuesday at Laurel Race Course because 
jockeys said Monday's rain and snow left the track too sloppy. 
</P>
<P>
The jockeys met after the fourth event on the card and decided to refuse to 
continue riding, citing excessive water on the track. 
</P>
<P>
Racing is expected to resume Thursday. Wednesdays are regularly off days at 
Laurel. 
