<P>
U.S. OLYMPIC SPORTS FESTIVAL TO BE HELD IN LOS ANGELES IN '91 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harry L. Usher, chairman of the U. S. Olympic Festival, announced preliminary 
plans Tuesday for the 1991 event, which will be held in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Usher said about 4,000 athletes will compete in 37 sports on July 12-21 in the 
U.S. Olympic Festival, formerly known as the National Sports Festival. 
</P>
<P>
As in the last Olympics held here, the athletes' quarters will be at USC and 
UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
Venue sites are still tentative, according to Elizabeth M. Primrose, president 
of the 11th Olympic Festival. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. was the host city for the 1932 and 1984 Olympic Games, and Usher said the 
city is aiming to lure the Olympics back in 2004. 
</P>
