the company's annual shareholders meeting at the Beverly Hilton. Barbakow's 
announcement signifies that MGM/UA, which has been trying to sell itself for 
more than a year, appears to be moving back into the movie-making business. 
MGM/UA had drastically cut back its production and development activities. MGM 
released 26 movies in 1989. 
