<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: BANKING/FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Compiled by James S. Granelli / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Business Loans: Liberty National Bank in Huntington Beach was the nation's 
10th-largest provider of business loans backed by the Small Business 
Administration during the government's fiscal year, which ended Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
The small bank, with assets of $132.6 million, provided $24.5 million in 
SBA-guaranteed loans to small companies. 
</P>
<P>
Providing loans to small business helps them grow, creates new jobs, increases 
the general tax base and helps firms bring their products and services to the 
marketplace, said Liberty President Philip S. Inglee. 
</P>
<P>
"It's taken us seven years to reach the top 10," he said. "We've been slowly 
moving up the ladder." Compiled by James S. Granelli / Times staff writer 
</P>
</TEXT>
