<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Larry Hanson and Terry Noonan have been appointed to the newly created position 
of executive vice president of Furon, a Laguna Niguel-based manufacturer of 
polymer components formerly known as Fluorocarbon. 
</P>
<P>
Both had previously been group vice presidents. Hanson will be responsible for 
Furon's fluid-sealing and advanced-polymers groups. Noonan will be responsible 
for the extrusion-technologies group, the engineered-products group and the CHR 
division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
