<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fire Loss -- Insurance covered the majority of costs resulting from a 1985 fire 
at the Huntington Art Gallery. 
</P>
<P>
A Friday article on conservation of fire-damaged art erroneously reported that 
about half of the Huntington's $1-million bill for cleanup and renovation was 
paid by government grants and that private donations covered the rest. In fact, 
the Huntington received an emergency grant of $30,000 from the National 
Endowment for the Humanities and a grant of $17,500 from the National Endowment 
for the Arts. Individuals, foundations and corporations contributed an 
additional $72,000. Insurance covered damage to the building. 
</P>
</TEXT>
