<P>
HONECKER HAS TUMOR REMOVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WEST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former East German leader Erich Honecker underwent a successful operation for a 
malignant kidney tumor today, the official East German news agency ADN 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
Doctors had said Honecker, under investigation on charges of profiteering and 
abuses of power during his 18 years as East Germany's hard-line Communist 
leader, had been too ill to be jailed and he was released from house arrest 
last week. It was not immediately clear whether Honecker, 77, would be jailed 
after his recuperation. 
</P>
<P>
ADN, quoting a Health Ministry spokesman, said, "The tumor was radically 
removed. The operation was carried out successfully." 
</P>
</TEXT>
