<P>
VIET REPATRIATION TO RESUME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Britain's enforced repatriation of Vietnamese boat people refused refugee 
status in Hong Kong will resume shortly despite U.S. opposition, government 
sources said today. 
</P>
<P>
British authorities hope that the move will deter another wave of boat people 
setting out for Hong Kong in February and March when sea conditions will permit 
a fresh exodus from Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
