<P>
MIDWEST EXPRESS AIRLINES TO INITIATE FLIGHTS TO CALIFORNIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MILWAUKEE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Midwest Express Airlines today announced that it will begin service from 
Milwaukee to Los Angeles, San Francisco and San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The expansion will be a giant step for the 5 1/2-year-old airline. 
</P>
<P>
The carrier has flown only as far west as Denver. 
</P>
<P>
Nonstop service to Los Angeles and direct service to San Diego will begin March 
1. Direct service means there are stops, but passengers do not have to change 
planes. 
</P>
<P>
It will add nonstop service to San Francisco and another direct flight to Los 
Angeles on March 19. 
</P>
<P>
The service will create 107 jobs at the airline, bringing its total employment 
to 827, a spokeswoman for Midwest Express said. Of that total, 714 are based in 
Milwaukee, where the airline is headquartered. 
</P>
